    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Natural Forests</h2>
        <p>Natural forests are rich ecosystems that serve as a home for countless species of plants and animals. They maintain ecological balance and provide a vital space for wildlife to thrive.</p>
        <img src="https://source.unsplash.com/800x400/?forest,nature" alt="A lush green forest">
    </section>
    <section id="importance">
        <h2>Importance of Co-Living</h2>
        <p>The co-living of animals and forests ensures biodiversity, promotes natural cycles like pollination, and keeps the ecosystem resilient against climate change.</p>
        <img src="https://source.unsplash.com/800x400/?wildlife,biodiversity" alt="Wildlife and biodiversity in a forest">
    </section>
    <section id="challenges">
        <h2>Challenges to Co-Living</h2>
        <p>Deforestation, urbanization, and climate change threaten the balance of natural habitats, leading to loss of biodiversity and disruption of ecosystems.</p>
        <img src="https://source.unsplash.com/800x400/?deforestation,climate-change" alt="Deforestation impact on the environment">
    </section>
    <section id="solutions">
        <h2>Solutions for Harmony</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Protecting natural forests through conservation efforts</li>
            <li>Creating wildlife corridors to connect fragmented habitats</li>
            <li>Promoting sustainable development and reforestation</li>
        </ul>
        <img src="https://source.unsplash.com/800x400/?reforestation,eco-friendly" alt="Reforestation and conservation efforts">
    </section>
